HEADWORD: Pencraft
<hw>Pen"craft</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Penmanship; skill in writing; chirography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of composing or writing;
authorship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would not give a groat for that person's knowledge in
<qex>pencraft</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1060 --></p>

<p><ent>Pend</ent>⟦br⟧
